<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3373] File install logging doesn&apos;t notify user of important errors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3373</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a bundle cannot be installed, no error is added to the log. Similarly, problems with jarring a directory are not logged as errors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the same time, logging is disabled by default. I would expect it to be set to the ERROR level, and only log important errors once.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12545146">FELIX-3373</key>
            <summary>File install logging doesn&apos;t notify user of important errors</summary>
